##DESeq2 LRT
##Without naive group
##https://hbctraining.github.io/DGE_workshop_salmon/lessons/08_DGE_LRT.html
library(DESeq2)
setwd("/stor/scratch/WCAAR/gayatri_scratch/Tagseq_Hiseq_MmPFC_JA19302/Concat_fastq/Star_trimmed/Htseq_counts")
directory<-("/stor/scratch/WCAAR/gayatri_scratch/Tagseq_Hiseq_MmPFC_JA19302/Concat_fastq/Star_trimmed/Htseq_counts")
sampleinfo<-read.csv("DeSEQ_sample_key_BeckerPFC_hiseqwithoutnaive.csv",header=TRUE)
SampleName <- sampleinfo$Sample
Group <-sampleinfo$Group
Time <-sampleinfo$Time2
sampleFiles <- grep(".count.sorted.txt",list.files(directory),value=TRUE)
sampleTable <- data.frame(sampleName = SampleName,fileName = sampleFiles,Group = Group,Time=Time)
#head(sampleTable)
#write.csv(sampleTable,file='sampletable_deseq2.csv')
##As the count files were labelled A,B,C,D they were getting that order. Here I had to manually change to get the Air,cie,fss,Cie_fss
sampleTable<-as.data.frame(read.csv("sampletable_deseq2.csv",header=TRUE))
head(sampleTable)

dds <- DESeqDataSetFromHTSeqCount(sampleTable = sampleTable,directory = directory, design = ~Group + Time + Group:Time)
dim(dds)
## [1] 56442    96
##remove the erccs otherwise would see PCA plot of the spikedin samples grouped together
dds<- dds[-(56351:56442)]
dim(dds)
## [1] 56350    96
con <- as.character(colData(dds)$Group)

### make sure to get fold change vs Control
colData(dds)$Group <- factor(con, levels = c("CTL","CIE","FSS","CIE_FSS"))
dds$Group <- relevel (dds$Group, "CTL")
dds_lrt_time <- DESeq(dds, test="LRT", reduced = ~ Group + Time)
res_LRT <- results(dds_lrt_time)


##Annotate LRT results     
library(biomaRt)
library(dplyr)
ensembl <- useMart(biomart="ensembl", dataset="mmusculus_gene_ensembl",host="www.ensembl.org")
annot<-getBM(c("ensembl_gene_id_version","ensembl_gene_id", "mgi_symbol", "chromosome_name", "strand", "start_position", "end_position","gene_biotype"),values= rownames(res_LRT), mart=ensembl)
idx<- match(rownames(res_LRT),annot$ensembl_gene_id_version)
res_LRT_gene <- data.frame(cbind(res_LRT, annot[idx,]))
write.csv(res_LRT_gene,file='Anova_Deseq2_lrt_genesymbol.csv')

##Clustering       
library(tidyverse)
library(dplyr)
##https://anaconda.org/bioconda/bioconductor-degreport/files 1.19.1. I had to stick to this version to have same results as Sean worked on.
library(DEGreport)
library(cluster)
library(cowplot)


# Subset the LRT results to return genes with padj < 0.05
sig_res_LRT <- res_LRT %>%
               data.frame() %>%
               rownames_to_column(var="gene") %>% 
               as_tibble() %>% 
               filter(padj < 0.05)
 
# Get sig gene lists
sigLRT_genes <- sig_res_LRT %>% 
                pull(gene)
                
length(sigLRT_genes)
## [1] 292
# Subset results for faster cluster finding 
clustering_sig_genes <- sig_res_LRT %>%
                  arrange(padj) %>%
                  head(n=292)


##rld
rld <- rlog(dds_lrt_time, blind=TRUE)
DESeq2::plotPCA(rld, intgroup=c("Group","Time"))

rldmat <- assay(rld) 

# Obtain rlog values for those significant genes
cluster_rlog <- rldmat[clustering_sig_genes$gene,]
dim(cluster_rlog)
## [1] 292  96
#292 7

##Time Group effect
design <-as.data.frame(colData(rld))
design$group <- factor(paste0(design$Time,"_",design$Group))
design$group<-factor(design$group, as.character(unique(design$group)))
class(design$Time)
## [1] "integer"
##Summary_clusters_Group
clusters <- degPatterns(cluster_rlog, metadata =design, time = "group", col="Group",minc=1,eachStep=TRUE)

##https://lpantano.github.io/DEGreport/reference/degPlotCluster.html
#clusters$df$cluster <- paste("Group",clusters$df$cluster, sep = ":")
##FOR Manuscript PLOT
## Make changes in the function, replace Group with Cluster 
source("degPlotCluster.R")
library(tibble)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
table <- rownames_to_column(as.data.frame(cluster_rlog), "genes") %>%
     gather("sample", "expression", -genes) %>%
     right_join(distinct(clusters$df[,c("genes", "cluster")]),
                by = "genes") %>%
     left_join(rownames_to_column(as.data.frame(design), "sample"),
               by = "sample") %>%
     as.data.frame()
d<-degPlotCluster(table, "group", "Group", process = TRUE,min_genes=1)
